Building the load generator locally:
    Install LMDB:
        git clone -b mdb.master git://git.openldap.org/openldap.git
        cd openldap/libraries/liblmdb
        make clean
        make install

    Compile the load generator:
        cd load-generator
        ./bootstrap
        ./configure LDFLAGS="-L/usr/local/lib" CPPFLAGS="-I/usr/local/include"
        make clean
        make


Running local generator in ec2:
    Install requirements locally
        sudo pip install -r requirements.txt

    Setup AWS credentials needed for EC2 access:
        Create ~/.boto:
            [Credentials]
            aws_access_key_id = YOURACCESSKEY
            aws_secret_access_key = YOURSECRETKEY

    Edit the fabfile.py:
        Change:
            env.ec2_key_pair_name
            env.ec2_vpc_id
            env.ec2_region

    Create instance:
        fab launch:testbox
        fab -H TESTBOX_IP configure_instance install_lmdb
        fab -H TESTBOX_IP compile_load_generator
